SIMPLE: suppose
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suppose
<hw>Sup*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Supposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Supposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>supposer</ets>; pref. <ets>sub-</ets> under + <ets>poser</ets> to
place; -- corresponding in meaning to L. <ets>supponere</ets>,
<ets>suppositum</ets>, to put under, to substitute, falsify,
counterfeit. See <er>Pose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To represent to
one's self, or state to another, not as true or real, but as if so, and
with a view to some consequence or application which the reality would
involve or admit of; to imagine or admit to exist, for the sake of
argument or illustration; to assume to be true; as, let us
<xex>suppose</xex> the earth to be the center of the system, what would
be the result?</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Suppose</qex> they take offence without a cause.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When we have as great assurance that a thing is, as we could
possibly, <qex>supposing</qex> it were, we ought not to make any doubt
of its existence.</q> <rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To imagine; to believe; to receive as
true.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How easy is a bush <qex>supposed</qex> a bear!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let not my lord <qex>suppose</qex> that they have slain all the
young men, the king's sons; for Amnon only is dead.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam.
xiii. 32.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To require to exist or to be true; to imply by the
laws of thought or of nature; <as>as, purpose <ex>supposes</ex>
foresight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One falsehood always <qex>supposes</qex> another, and renders all
you can say suspected.</q> <rj><qau>Female Quixote.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To put by fraud in the place of another.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To imagine; believe; conclude; judge; consider;
view; regard; conjecture; assume.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1450 --></p>

<p><ent>Suppose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suppose
<hw>Sup*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make
supposition; to think; to be of opinion.</def> <rj><au>Acts ii.
15.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Suppose
<hw>Sup*pose"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Supposition.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A base <xex>suppose</xex> that
he is honest.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supposeer</ent>⟦br⟧
